 # This file describes the installation of SpeciesGeoCoder on Mac OSX, 
# GNU/Linux and Windows systems.

===========================================
# Content of this file
1.) For the impatient 
2.) Dependencies
3.) Installing the GUI version
4.) Installing on Mac OSX
5.) Installing on Windows
6.) Installing on GNU/Linux
7.) Installing the development version
8.) Example data
===========================================

=====================
1.) For the impatient (if this doesn't work: try the other options!)
=====================
Downloade the latest version from https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/releases
unzip speciesgeocoder-x.x.x.zip
cd speciesgeocoder-x.x.x
./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif


=================
2.) Dependencies
=================
argparse (Module included in python v2.7. Available at https://pypi.python.org/pypi/argparse) 
osgeo (The GDAL library available at https://pypi.python.org/pypi/GDAL/)
R (only needed if you want to use the plot functions or do stochastic mapping. Available from http://www.r-project.org/)


==============================
3.) Installing SpeciesGeoCoder with a Graphical User Interface (GUI)
==============================
The recomended way of running SpeciesGeoCoder is from the commandline, as that version of the code contains the latest bug fixes and features. However, a GUI for SpeciesGeoCoder (available for Windows, Mac OSX and GNU/Linux) with the basic functions of the program is available at http://sourceforge.net/projects/speciesgeocodergui/


==========================
4.) Installing on Mac OSX.
==========================

a. Downloade the latest version from https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/releases
b. Unzip the file by clicking on it.
c. Open a terminal window and use the command "cd" to move into the directory "speciesgeocoder-x.x.x" (where "x.x.x" will indicate the version number of the latest release).
d. Copy and paste the following command into your terminal window to make sure everything works as expected:

	./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif


=========================
5.) Installing on Windows
=========================

a. Download and install the Latest Python 2 Release from https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/
b. Direct your browser to http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/ and then download and install GDAL for python 2.7
c. Download and install R from http://cran.r-project.org/bin/windows/base/

   In addition, you'll also have to add the R executables to your PATH (in order for SpeciesGeoCoder to find it).
   I. 	Find the directory that the R program is installed in (e.g "C:\Program Files\R\R-3.1.1")
   II. 	From the desktop, right-click My Computer and click Properties.
   III.	In the System Properties window, click on the Advanced tab.
   IV.	In the Advanced section, click the Environment Variables button.
   V.	Click the Environment Variables button, highlight the Path variable in the Systems Variable section and click the Edit button. 
   VI.	Add ";C:\Program Files\R\R-3.1.1\bin" (if that is where the R executables are found, dont forget the preceding ";" character) to the end of line and ckick "Ok".

Change permissions to the R "library" directory in the following way: (this is nessesary as SpeciesGeoCoder will have to automatically install additional R packages).

d. Right click on "C:\Program Files\R\R-3.1.1\library" and select properties -> Security.
e. Click "Edit".
f. In "Group our user names" select your name.
g. Mark the "Full control" checkbox.
h. Click "Ok".


===========================
6.) Installing on GNU/Linux
===========================
Downloade the latest version from https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/releases
unzip speciesgeocoder-x.x.x.zip
cd speciesgeocoder-x.x.x
./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif

Optionally you can make a symbolic link from a directory in your PATH to the file "speciesgeocoder" in the "speciesgeocoder-x.x.x" directory. 


======================================
7.) Installing the development version
======================================
git clone git@github.com:mtop/speciesgeocoder.git
cd speciesgeocoder/


================
8.) Example data
================
Examples of the type of input files used by 'speciesgeocoder' is located in the directory "example_data/". You can test the program by typing the following command in the 'speciesgeocoder' directory.

./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif

